org.apache.flink.streaming.state

Class MapState<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flink.streaming.state.OperatorState<T>
      • org.apache.flink.streaming.state.PartitionableState<Map<K,V>>
        • org.apache.flink.streaming.state.MapState<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - The type of the keys.
    V - The type of the values.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Map<K,V>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GraphState

    public class MapState<K,V>
extends PartitionableState<Map<K,V>>
implements Map<K,V>
    A Map that can be used as a partitionable operator state, for both fault tolerance and rebalancing in Flink programs. The default repartitioner for this operator repartitions by the hashcodes of the keys in the map.

    The MapState also allows for incremental (data efficient) checkpointing of the state. The entries in the map should only be modified by using the dedicated methods: put(Object, Object),remove(Object), putAll(Map) and clear. Directly modifying the the entryset will cause errors when checkpointing.

      • repartition

        public OperatorState<Map<K,V>>[] repartition(int numberOfPartitions)
        Description copied from class: PartitionableState
        Repartitions(divides) the current state into the given number of new partitions. The created partitions will be used to redistribute then rebuild the state among the parallel instances of the operator. The implementation should reflect the partitioning of the input values to maintain correct operator behavior.

        It is also assumed that if we would PartitionableState.reBuild(org.apache.flink.streaming.state.OperatorState<T>...) the repartitioned state we would basically get the same as before.
        Specified by:
        repartition in class PartitionableState<Map<K,V>>
        Parameters:
        numberOfPartitions - The desired number of partitions. The method must return an array of that size.
        Returns:
        The array containing the state part for each partition.
